NAME
    re::engine::TRE - TRE regular expression engine

VERSION
    version 0.05

SYNOPSIS
        use re::engine::TRE;

        if ("mooh!" =~ /\([mo]*\)/) {
            say $1; # "moo"
        }

DESCRIPTION
    Replaces perl's regex engine in a given lexical scope with POSIX regular
    expressions provided by the TRE regular expression library. tre-0.8.0 is
    shipped with this module.

